AB We present a thermally reconflgurable silicon photonic logic gate capable of performing both OR and NOT operations within a single, highly compact device. Leveraging the thermo-optic effect of silicon and adjoint-based topology optimization, we co-optimize the structure for two distinct thermal states, 300 K and 600 K, corresponding to the logic behaviors of OR and NOT logic behaviors, respectively. The device operates in the transverse electric (TE) mode at telecom wavelengths and occupies a footprint of 2 um x 2 um, with feature sizes compatible with electron-beam lithography. This work exemplifies a dynamic and efficient design strategy to reconflgurable photonic logic and computing components, offering promising potential for the development of flexible and scalable optical computing architectures.
