AB High-speed optical logic gates are essential components for photonic integrated circuits (PICs) addressing the inherent constraints of electronic systems caused by their electron-based transport processes. Our study presents a reconfigurable optical logic gate utilizing adiabatically coupled waveguides (ACW) and indium tin oxide (ITO), leveraging its free carrier modulation and terahertz operational speed potential. The proposed architecture resulting in an 89% acceleration and a 98% reduction in power consumption relative to existing leading technologies in the implementation of XNOR-Net. These findings underscore the promise of ITO-based logic gates for high-performance, ultra-dense, and power-efficient integrated photonic circuits and next-generation photonic AI accelerators.
