TI 1T′-MoTe2 as an integrated saturable absorber for photonic
   machine learning
SO APPLIED PHYSICS LETTERS
LA English
DT Article
ID ABSORPTION; TRANSITION; GRAPHENE
AB We investigate the saturable absorption behavior of a 1T '-MoTe2 monolayer integrated with a silicon nitride waveguide for applications in photonic neural networks. Using experimental transmission measurements and theoretical modeling, we characterize the nonlinear response of the material. Our model, incorporating quasi-Fermi level separation and carrier dynamics, explains these behaviors and predicts the material's absorption dependence on the carrier density. Furthermore, we demonstrate a coupling efficiency of up to 20% between the 1T '-MoTe2 monolayer and the silicon nitride waveguide, with saturation achievable at input powers as low as a few microwatts. These results suggest that 1T '-MoTe2 is a promising candidate for implementing nonlinear functions in integrated photonic neural networks.
